<!-- Grants Help -->
<div class="help-section">
    <nav class="help-breadcrumb"><a href="/help">Help</a> / <span>Grants</span></nav>
    <h1><i class="fas fa-hand-holding-usd"></i> Grants</h1>
    <p class="help-intro">Manage grant awards, spending, and reporting.</p>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>What is a Grant?</h2>
        <p>A grant is a formal award of money from a foundation, government agency, or other organization for a specific purpose. Unlike general donations, grants typically have:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Specific spending restrictions</li>
            <li>Reporting requirements</li>
            <li>Time periods for spending</li>
            <li>Matching requirements (sometimes)</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Grant Fields</h2>
        <table class="help-table field-table">
            <tr><td><strong>Name</strong></td><td>Your internal name for the grant</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Grantor</strong></td><td>Who awarded the grant (FEMA, State, Foundation)</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Grant Number</strong></td><td>Official grant ID from grantor</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Amount</strong></td><td>Total award amount</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Start Date</strong></td><td>When grant period begins</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>End Date</strong></td><td>When grant period ends</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Status</strong></td><td>Pending, Active, Completed, Closed</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Restrictions</strong></td><td>What the money can be used for</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Reporting Requirements</strong></td><td>What reports are due and when</td></tr>
            <tr><td><strong>Next Report Due</strong></td><td>Date of next required report</td></tr>
        </table>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Common Fire Department Grants</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>FEMA AFG</strong> - Assistance to Firefighters Grant (equipment, training)</li>
            <li><strong>FEMA SAFER</strong> - Staffing for Adequate Fire & Emergency Response</li>
            <li><strong>State Fire Marshal Grants</strong> - Varies by state</li>
            <li><strong>Foundation Grants</strong> - Private foundations supporting fire service</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-block">
        <h2>Tracking Grant Spending</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Create the grant record with award details</li>
            <li>When spending grant funds, create expense transaction</li>
            <li>Link the expense to the grant</li>
            <li>System automatically tracks spending vs. award</li>
        </ol>
        <p>The grant detail page shows:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Award Amount</strong> - Total granted</li>
            <li><strong>Amount Used</strong> - Total spent so far</li>
            <li><strong>Remaining Balance</strong> - Left to spend</li>
            <li><strong>All Expenses</strong> - Linked transactions</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <div class="help-warning">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
        <strong>Critical:</strong> Always link grant expenses to the grant record. This is essential for compliance reporting!
    </div>
</div>
